Fossilised faeces suggests an ancient baby shark might have been killed by its dinner.

U.S. palaeontologists analysing a 70 million-year-old fossilised poo from an extinct newborn shark found it ate a baby turtle shortly before it died.

The researchers think the shark, living close to the South Carolina coastline, bit off more than it could digest and probably died as a result.

