Professor Schwimmer said: ‘It's possible the turtle was too much shell. [The shark] may have died from too much turtle.

While Professor Schwimmer is not sure about the exact species of the shark and turtle, he thinks the shark could be the extinct Squalicorax kaupi.

Scientists studying other shark coprolites have previously found some fish had tapeworms 270 million years ago.

